# objects(at:)

**Instance Method**

Returns an array containing the objects in the fetch result at the indexes in the specified index set.

## Declaration

```swift
func objects(at indexes: IndexSet) -> [ObjectType]
```

## Parameters

- **indexes**: An index set containing indexes within the bounds of the fetch result.

## Return Value

An array containing the objects in the fetch result at the indexes specified by `indexes`.

## Discussion

The ordering of the returned array follows the index set. That is, in the returned array, an object with a higher index in the index set comes after any object with a smaller index in the index set.

Raises a range exception if any index in the index set is beyond the end of the fetch result (that is, greater than or equal to the value of the [doc://com.apple.photokit/documentation/Photos/PHFetchResult/count] property).

## Querying a Fetch Result

- **contains(_:)**: Returns whether the specified object is present in the fetch result.
- **count**: The number of objects in the fetch result.
- **countOfAssets(with:)**: Returns the number of assets in the fetch result of a specified type.
- **firstObject**: The first object in the fetch result.
- **lastObject**: The last object in the fetch result.
- **object(at:)**: Returns the object located at the specified index.
- **subscript(_:)**: Returns the object located at the specified index.
